# FoodExpress development

## Local dev (fast)

- Prefer `npm run dev:local` — Postgres in Docker only; API (`:3001`) and Vite (`:5180`) run natively with hot reload.
- API env: `server/.env` (copy from `server/.env.example`). Never commit `.env` files.
- Frontend uses Vite proxy: `VITE_API_URL=/api` in `.env.development`.

## Demo data

- `npm run seed:demo` — re-seeds orders, promos, and inbox messages (idempotent, tagged `demoSeed`).
- Demo logins: `admin@foodexpress.com` / `Admin@12345`, `customer@foodexpress.com` / `Customer@123`.

## Docker (production-like)

- Full stack: `docker compose up -d --build` (needs strong secrets in root `.env`).
- Dev DB only: `docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml -p foodie-dev up -d db`.

## Code layout

- Frontend: `src/` (React + Vite + Tailwind v4)
- API: `server/src/` (Express + Postgres)
- Seeds: `server/seed/*.json`, demo orders in `server/src/db/seedDemoData.js`
